{
  "name": ".AM-1: Ingest",
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "description": "Morning data collection: Slack scan + Asana task pull + activity monitor + email scan. Read-only. Produces intake files + morning snapshot for AM-2 and EOD-2.",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run AM-1: Ingest. PURE DATA COLLECTION. No drafting, no decisions, no organ writes.\n\nCONTEXT LOAD: spine.md, current.md, slack-channel-registry.json, slack-scan-state.json, asana-command-center.md.\n\nSLACK SCAN: list_channels (unreadOnly=true). Sort by mention_count then section. Apply depth rules. Relevance Filter (threshold 25). Produce slack-digest in intake/. RSW-CHANNEL INTAKE. PROACTIVE SEARCH. Update scan state. DuckDB batch writes.\n\nASANA PULL (replaces old email-bridge sync): Use Enterprise Asana MCP directly.\n1. SearchTasksInWorkspace: assignee_any=1212732742544167, completed=false, sort_by=due_date.\n2. For each task, GetTaskDetails with opt_fields: name,due_on,completed,custom_fields.name,custom_fields.display_value,custom_fields.enum_value.name,projects.name,notes,permalink_url.\n3. Categorize by Routine field: Sweep (1213608836755503), Core Two (1213608836755504), Engine Room (1213608836755505), Admin (1213608836755506), Backlog (no Routine set).\n4. Flag: Priority_RW=Today tasks, overdue tasks, tasks with no Routine (needs triage).\n5. Write asana-digest to intake/ with categorized task list.\n6. Check for new tasks since last scan (tasks in Recently Assigned section or created in last 24h).\n7. MORNING SNAPSHOT: Write categorized task state to ~/shared/context/active/asana-morning-snapshot.json with structure: {snapshot_date: YYYY-MM-DD, tasks: [{gid, name, routine, priority_rw, due_on, completed}], bucket_counts: {sweep: N, core: N, engine_room: N, admin: N, backlog: N}, today_tasks: [GIDs where Priority_RW=Today], overdue_tasks: [GIDs where due_on < today]}. This snapshot is the frozen baseline for EOD-2 reconciliation.\n\nACTIVITY MONITOR (run after Asana pull): Follow protocol at ~/shared/context/active/asana-activity-monitor-protocol.md.\n1. Read ~/shared/context/active/asana-scan-state.json for last scan timestamps.\n2. For each incomplete task from the Asana pull above, call GetTaskStories to detect teammate activity since last scan. Skip stories authored by Richard (GID 1212732742544167).\n3. Classify stories: comment_added (💬 text + author + task), due_date_changed (📅 old→new + who), reassigned (👤 new assignee + who).\n4. Write all detected signals to ~/shared/context/intake/asana-activity.md (overwrite each scan). Format: scan timestamp, tasks scanned count, signals detected count, then sections for 💬 Comments, 📅 Due Date Changes, 👤 Reassignments.\n5. Update ~/shared/context/active/asana-scan-state.json with new per-task timestamps and last_scan_timestamp.\n6. If GetTaskStories fails for a task (rate limit, API error), log error, skip task, continue. Note skipped tasks at bottom of output.\n\nEMAIL SCAN: Catalog unread. Produce email-triage in intake/. SKIP Auto-Comms folder Asana emails — no longer needed.\n\nREPORT: Channels scanned, signals, Asana tasks pulled (by Routine bucket + overdue count), morning snapshot written (task count + bucket counts), activity signals detected (comments/due changes/reassignments), emails triaged. Feeds AM-2."
  }
}
